session:
  updated: 2026-07-12
  status: init_lifecycle_strengthened
  branch: init-lifecycle

goal:
  current: make /specialise a complete repository-specialisation lifecycle

completed:
  - canonical repository operating contract with all required sections
  - composable lazy-loaded skill system
  - evidence-driven project discovery
  - project profile with structured unknowns and explicit infrastructure decision
  - hybrid agent topology with agent-team-fallback skill
  - token-efficient coordination
  - model routing with handoff protocol
  - lightweight SDD
  - test-first workflow
  - testing trophy specialisation
  - SQL migration policy
  - init orchestration with discover->decide->specialise->rewrite->validate->handoff phases
  - build-container specialisation with explicit container decision policy
  - infra-local-compose specialisation with health checks and deterministic cleanup
  - infra-decision skill for explicit IaC status
  - tooling and MCP discovery
  - Nix environment
  - CI and repo checks
  - script-based command dispatcher with ready, compose-config, compose-test, infra-check
  - check-readme validation
  - project-ready deterministic readiness check
  - reconcile-delivery workflow skill
  - agent-team-fallback coordination skill
  - worktree scaffolding under .worktrees/
  - template README and AGENTS source material under .agentic-template/templates/
  - repository-local knowledge wiki and validation

in_progress: []

next:
  - extend self-test with positive and negative fixtures for readiness
  - validate full test suite
  - open PR with concise summary and test evidence

decisions:
  - id: project_concept_date
    summary: 2026-05-16 is recorded as the project concept date
  - id: composable_skills
    summary: init orchestrates lazy-loaded bounded skills
  - id: evidence_driven_bootstrap
    summary: infer and recommend before asking human preference questions
  - id: project_profile
    summary: separate project facts, inferences, decisions and unknowns
  - id: clean_architecture_bias
    summary: protect meaningful volatility boundaries without ceremonial layering
  - id: testing_trophy
    summary: favour fast feedback plus strong integration confidence
  - id: canonical_project_script
    summary: .agentic-template/bin/project is the canonical hidden command surface; no template Makefile
  - id: repository_local_knowledge_layer
    summary: .agents/knowledge stores durable knowledge and proposals; HANDOFF stays active state
  - id: explicit_container_decision
    summary: every project makes an explicit container decision; deployable services default to tested image
  - id: explicit_infra_decision
    summary: every project records local_topology, deployment_target and iac status
  - id: readiness_command
    summary: project ready runs all applicable deterministic checks with PASS/NOT APPLICABLE/FAIL summary
  - id: delivery_reconciliation
    summary: reconcile-delivery skill compares specs and docs against delivered repository
  - id: agent_team_fallback
    summary: graceful degradation preserves acceptance and review gates; single agent is not independent team
  - id: model_fallback_handoff
    summary: model or provider changes require handoff update with fixed decisions and test results

risks:
  - constrained TOON validation is intentionally incomplete
  - framework detection remains evidence-based inference
  - plugin discovery may be advisory
  - MCP discovery must remain secret-safe
  - knowledge validation is lightweight Markdown frontmatter parsing
  - project-ready container and compose checks require docker availability

